#train-test Random size
#spl <- runif(62)
#train <- subset(colon, spl<=0.75)
#test <- subset(colon, spl>0.75)
#train-test explicit size
ind <- sample(1:62,size = 50)
train <- colon[ind,]
test <- colon[-ind,]

:

\[\begin{equation} \Pr(C|X) = \frac{\Pr(X|C)\Pr(C)}{\Pr(X)} \end{equation}\]

X :

\[\begin{equation} \Pr(C|x_1,x_2,...,x_{2000}) = \frac{\Pr(x_1,x_2,...,x_{2000}|C)\Pr(C)}{\Pr(x_1,x_2,...,x_{2000})} \end{equation}\]

:

\[\begin{equation} \Pr(C|x_1,x_2,...,x_{2000}) = \Pr(C)\Pi_{i=1}^{2000}\Pr(x_i|C) \end{equation}\]

:

\[\begin{equation} \Pr(X_i=x_i|C=c_j) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}\sigma}\exp{(-\frac{(x_i-\mu)^2}{2\sigma^2})} \end{equation}\]

: 

#cancer probability
cprob <- sum(train$cancer==1)/dim(train)[1]
hprob <- 1-cprob
ctrain <- subset(train,train$cancer==1)
htrain <- subset(train,train$cancer==-1)
hmean <- sapply(htrain[,2:2001], mean)
hsd <- sapply(htrain[,2:2001], sd)
cmean <- sapply(ctrain[,2:2001], mean)
csd <- sapply(ctrain[,2:2001], sd)
target = c()
for (i in 1:nrow(test)) {
p1 = cprob
p2 = hprob
  for (j in 1:2000) {
    p1 = p1*dnorm(test[[i,j+1]],cmean[j],csd[j],log = F)
    p2 = p2*dnorm(test[[i,j+1]],hmean[j],hsd[j],log = F)
  }
if(p1>p2){
  target = c(target,1)
}else{
  target = c(target,-1)
}
}
